<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q52_v7" title="Q52_v7" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>
      Se define una traslación T en el plano cartesiano: a cualquier punto representado por
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>,</m:mo>
          <m:mi>y</m:mi>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mo>→</m:mo>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>-</m:mo>
          <m:mn>4</m:mn>
          <m:mo>,</m:mo>
          <m:mi>y</m:mi>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:mn>1</m:mn>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>.
      Uno de los vértices de un cuadrilátero es el punto
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mi>A</m:mi>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn>
          <m:mo>,</m:mo>
          <m:mo>-</m:mo>
          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>.
    </p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-prompt>
        ¿Cuáles son las coordenadas de la imagen de este punto, es decir, del punto
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mi>A</m:mi>
              <m:mo>'</m:mo>
            </m:msup>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>, al aplicar esta traslación?
      </qti-prompt>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mn>7</m:mn>
            <m:mo>,</m:mo>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>1</m:mn>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La traslación cambia cada punto de la forma (x, y) a (x − 4, y + 1). Para A(3, −2), se obtiene x = 3 − 4 = −1 e y = −2 + 1 = −1. Por lo tanto, la imagen es (−1, −1), no (7, −1).</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>1</m:mn>
            <m:mo>,</m:mo>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>1</m:mn>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! La traslación indica restar 4 a la coordenada x y sumar 1 a la coordenada y. Desde A(3, −2): 3 − 4 = −1 y −2 + 1 = −1. Entonces la imagen es A′(−1, −1).</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>1</m:mn>
            <m:mo>,</m:mo>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>3</m:mn>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La regla de traslación es (x, y) → (x − 4, y + 1). Para A(3, −2), la primera coordenada queda 3 − 4 = −1, pero la segunda debe ser −2 + 1 = −1. Por eso la imagen correcta es (−1, −1), no (−1, −3).</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mn>7</m:mn>
            <m:mo>,</m:mo>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>3</m:mn>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al aplicar la traslación a A(3, −2), se calcula x = 3 − 4 = −1 e y = −2 + 1 = −1. Así, el punto imagen es (−1, −1). La opción (7, −3) no coincide con estos resultados.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar la regla de traslación</strong></p>
            <p>La transformación lleva cada punto
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
              al punto
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>.
            </p>
            <p>Esto significa: a la coordenada <strong>x</strong> se le resta 4 y a la coordenada <strong>y</strong> se le suma 1.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Reemplazar las coordenadas del punto A</strong></p>
            <p>El punto dado es
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>A</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>.
            </p>
            <p>Entonces
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
              y
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Calcular la nueva coordenada x</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Calcular la nueva coordenada y</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 5: Escribir el punto imagen</strong></p>
            <p>La imagen del punto es
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi>A</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>'</m:mo>
                  </m:msup>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>.
            </p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, la alternativa correcta es <strong>ChoiceB</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>